                                                                            <comments>
                            <comment id="448552" author="adilger" created="Tue, 18 Mar 2025 06:42:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Usage of fstrim in test scripts added in patch &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/54720&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/54720&lt;/a&gt; (&quot;&lt;tt&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-17722&quot; title=&quot;wait_delete_completed() to trim underlying fs backed by tmpfs&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-17722&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-17722&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; tests: trim tmpfs from wait_delete_completed()&lt;/tt&gt;&quot;)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="257118" author="adilger" created="Sat, 26 Oct 2019 06:23:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;We never did get a test out of &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-11355&quot; title=&quot;Add Lustre trim support&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-11355&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-11355&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; so reopening this ticket to track adding an &lt;tt&gt;fstrim&lt;/tt&gt; regression test.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="216757" author="adilger" created="Tue, 19 Dec 2017 18:43:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This should be put into a test script, rather than be done by hand, so that it can be run in the future, possibly as a regular part of autotest. It is possible to check if the underlying device is an SSD by checking &lt;tt&gt;/sys/block/&amp;lt;device&amp;gt;/queue/rotational&lt;/tt&gt; is &lt;tt&gt;0&lt;/tt&gt;. The test would be skipped if this is 1.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
